        "Name" : "Engine Linear",
        "Details" : "In an effort to increase power-weight ratio (and thus, reduce engine weight for a given rating) of fusion engines without increasing fragility of the carrying 'mech, Toho Heavy Industries has developed the Linear Fusion Engine. Rather than a spherical containment unit which can extend into the side torso bays, this engine utilizes linear fusion technology, which allows for the power plant and containment unit to be built as a vertical 'stack'. This incidentally somewhat reduces sensors signature, as the engine naturally accelerates half the fusion reaction waste byproducts straight into the ground. The other end is heavily shielded, to avoid irradiating the 'MechWarrior & cockpit electronics, but increases heat generation, making these engines unpopular for forces without access to advanced engine sink kits.",
